    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - 2000, 4000, 8000 - DESCRIPTION - GRILLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="6">
        <title>GRILLE</title>
        <para>The grille on the 2000 series and 8200 model can be removed without removing the hood. The grille on the
            4000 series (except stationary grille) and 8100 model has a one-piece integral fiberglass grille bonded to
            the hood, and painted the same color as the hood (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900217">Figure 17</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900218">Figure 18</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900219">Figure 19</hotlnk>, and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900220">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900217" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900217.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 17. 2500 and 2600 Model Grille (Original Hood)</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900218" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900218.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 18. 2600 Model Grille (After March 1996) and 8200 Model Grille</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. UPPER GRILLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LOWER GRILLE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900219" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 19. 4000 Series One-Piece Hood and Grille</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900220" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900220.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 20. 8100 Model One-Piece Hood and Grille</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The 2500 and 2600 models with original hood and 4000 series have an optional stationary grille mounted to
            the radiator for applications that require the mounting of crank shaft driven hydraulic pump, or other
            similar front mounted equipment. The optional stationary grille can be removed from the radiator (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900221">Figure 21</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900222">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900221" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900221.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 21. 2500 and 2600 Models (Original Hood with Stationary Grille)</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900222" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900222.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 22. 4000 Series with Stationary Grille</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
